org.webcurator.core.util
Class LockManager

java.lang.Object
  org.webcurator.core.util.LockManager

public class LockManager
extends java.lang.Object

The LockManager is responsible for managing Pessimistic locks. This has not been used in version 1.0 of the Web Curator Tool and must be thoroughly tested before use.

Author:
bbeaumont

releaseLocksForOwner

public void releaseLocksForOwner(java.lang.String owner)
Release all locks held by the user. This is to be called when their session is destroyed to ensure that they do not hold locks unnecessarily.

Parameters:
owner - The user to release the locks for.
